nt Activities and Events</h2><div class="news-item"><h3>Spring Outing to Local Park</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>Our residents enjoyed a beautiful day at the local park. These outings are an important part of our residents' social engagement and connection to their community.</p></div><div class="news-item"><h3>Monthly Game and Puzzle Afternoon</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>Residents gathered for games and puzzles. These activities promote mental engagement, social connection, and fun.</p></div></div><div class="news-section"><h2>Service and Policy Updates</h2><div class="news-item"><h3>Extended Visiting Hours</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>Family visiting hours have been extended to 8am to 6pm, seven days a week. Family connection is vital to resident well-being.</p></div><div class="news-item"><h3>New Safety Protocols in Place</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>We've implemented updated safety protocols and emergency procedures. All staff have completed training.</p></div></div><div class="news-section"><h2>Staff and Team News</h2><div class="news-item"><h3>Welcome New Caregiver</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>Please welcome Sarah, our newest caregiver. She brings compassion, experience, and dedication to our team.</p></div><div class="news-item"><h3>Staff Training Milestone</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>Our entire caregiving team has completed advanced dementia-care training.</p></div></div><div class="news-section"><h2>Seasonal and Community-Focused Content</h2><div class="news-item"><h3>Spring Wellness Reminder</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>As spring arrives, remember to stay hydrated, get light exercise, and protect yourself from seasonal allergies.</p></div><div class="news-item"><h3>Flu Shot Clinic Coming Soon</h3><div class="news-date">April 2026</div><p>We'll be hosting a seasonal flu-shot clinic for our residents. Vaccinations are an important part of 